############################################################
#
#  wavreader.cpp: reads .wav files
#
############################################################


This code is based on K. L. Srinivas' work: http://www.ee.iitb.ac.in/daplab/resources/wav_read_write.cpp using all the specification in https://ccrma.stanford.edu/courses/422/projects/WaveFormat/

wavreader.cpp has been tested on Linux OS using g++ compiler.

Use: "make"
to compile.
The command g++ wavreader.cpp -o wavreader has been implemented.

Use: "make clean"
to clean the previous compilation.
